tr.td: All parameters are within normal limits except for a low HbA1c (3.4%), which may suggest recent hypoglycemia, anemia, or altered red cell turnover. Glucose is normal, and renal, electrolyte, and lipid profiles are unremarkable. Correlate low HbA1c with clinical context; consider further evaluation if symptoms or risk factors are present.
